5:{s:4:\"data\";s:350:\"The default settings for the installation of WebsiteDefender on your site require the Agent to be installed in the website&#8217;s root directory. For the less-knowledgeable users among you, the root or &#8216;/&#8217; of a website is the top-most directory which contains all the files and subfolders of the site. When you connect to your site [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Jacques G\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1651:\"<p>The default settings for the installation of WebsiteDefender on your site require the Agent to be installed in the website&#8217;s root directory. For the less-knowledgeable users among you, the root or &#8216;/&#8217; of a website is the top-most directory which contains all the files and subfolders of the site.</p>\n<p>When you connect to your site via <a title=\"File Transfer Protocol\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File_Transfer_Protocol\" target=\"_blank\">FTP</a> or through your host&#8217;s admin dashboard, you will be able to see a structure of files and folders containing all the bits and pieces necessary for your site to work. Most commonly, the root directory will be the one which contains your site&#8217;s homepage, which is usually called &#8216;index&#8217;. If your site is built on <a title=\"PHP\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PHP\" target=\"_blank\">PHP</a> the homepage should be called &#8216;index.php&#8217;, likewise if your site is an ASP application then the homepage will be called &#8216;index.asp&#8217; and so forth&#8230;</p>\n<p>In the screenshot below, you can see how the file &#8216;index.php&#8217; is located in the &#8216;/&#8217; (or root) directory of the WordPress site, shown in the &#8216;Remote site&#8217; area of the FTP client being used. This is where the WebsiteDefender Agent should normally be installed.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/root.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1714\" title=\"Root Directory\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/root-300x175.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"175\" /></a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/where-is-site-root-directory/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"Why can’t I log on to the dashboard after changing my password?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/logon-failed-after-changing-password/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/logon-failed-after-changing-password/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";