ontent/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2426:\"<p>The WebsiteDefender support team have received several reports from users being locked out of their dashboard after changing the password. The development team is working on resolving the problem, however there is a workaround which solves the issue until the fix is implemented.</p>\n<p>If you cannot access the dashboard after changing your password, clearing your web browser&#8217;s cache and history will allow you to log in again. The following section explains how this can be done for the latest versions of today&#8217;s most common browsers:</p>\n<p><strong>Google Chrome</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Select the <strong>Wrench</strong> icon (the settings menu, located in the upper-right corner) then <strong>Tools</strong> &gt; <strong>Clear Browsing Data</strong>&#8230;.</li>\n<li>Select the <strong>Empty the cache</strong> and <strong>Clear browsing history</strong> check-boxes. Uncheck everything else to avoid deleting data unintentionally.</li>\n<li>In the <strong>Obliterate the following items from:</strong> dropdown menu, select <strong>the beginning of time</strong>.</li>\n<li>Click the <strong>Clear Browsing Data</strong> button, and wait a few moments for the task to complete.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Mozilla Firefox</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click the Firefox menu in the top left corner. Select the right arrow next to <strong>History</strong>, and then click <strong>Clear Recent History</strong>.</li>\n<li>Make sure <strong>Details</strong> is expanded, then select <strong>Cache</strong> and <strong>Browsing &amp; Download History</strong> from the list. Uncheck everything else.</li>\n<li>In the <strong>Time Range to Clear:</strong> drop down, select <strong>Everything</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Clear Now</strong>, and wait a few moments for the task to complete.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Microsoft Internet Explorer</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click the gear at the top right to open the settings menu. Select <strong>Safety</strong> &gt; <strong>Delete Browsing History</strong>&#8230;</li>\n<li>Select the <strong>Temporary Internet Files</strong> and <strong>History</strong> checkboxes. You will also need to uncheck all the other boxes, especially Preserve Favorites website data.</li>\n<li>Click the <strong>Delete</strong> button near the bottom of the window to perform the operations (i.e. clear your cache by deleting temporary files), and wait a few moments for the task to complete.</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/logon-failed-after-changing-password/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"How exactly does WebsiteDefender monitor my site?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/how-does-websitedefender-work/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/how-does-websitedefender-work/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"