l_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"websitedefender wordpress security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/?p=1821\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:405:\"After taking over the two most popular WordPress security plugins: WP Security Scan and Secure WordPress, we are pleased to announce the release of WebsiteDefender WordPress Security plugin, which brings together the best features from the other two plugins into a new and more capable tool to help you secure your WordPress installation with minimum effort. In case you&#8217;re wondering, WP [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Jacques G\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5879:\"<p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1825\" title=\"wsd\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/wsd1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"188\" height=\"166\" /></p>\n<p>After taking over the two most popular WordPress security plugins: <strong>WP Security Scan</strong> and <strong>Secure WordPress</strong>, we are pleased to announce the release of <strong><a title=\"WP Security Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/websitedefender-wordpress-security\" target=\"_blank\">WebsiteDefender WordPress Security plugin</a></strong>, which brings together the best features from the other two plugins into a new and more capable tool to help you secure your WordPress installation with minimum effort. In case you&#8217;re wondering, <a title=\"Wp Security Scan\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-security-scan/\" target=\"_blank\">WP Security Scan</a> and <a title=\"Secure WordPress\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/secure-wordpress\" target=\"_blank\">Secure WordPress</a> will still be available, however we encourage you to take a look at the new exciting features we&#8217;ve built into <a title=\"WP Security Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/websitedefender-wordpress-security\" target=\"_blank\">WebsiteDefender WordPress Security</a>.</p>\n<h2>Easy to use, and now easy to secure</h2>\n<p>Although the WordPress platform is well known for ease-of-use and speedy configuration, securing your website can still consume lots of precious time when one considers all the possible issues that put your site and data at risk. <a title=\"WebsiteDefender WordPress Security\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/websitedefender-wordpress-security\" target=\"_blank\">WebsiteDefender WordPress Security</a> takes care of doing all the rounds by checking your WordPress installation, site files, and database, for a complete assessment and report on how to correct any security issues with the way your site is configured.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/wsd_wp_report.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1836\" title=\"Security Report\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/wsd_wp_report-300x165.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"165\" /></a></p>\n<pre style=\"text-align: center;\">fig.01 - A post-scan security report</pre>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>So, in a nutshell, the following list highlights the security tools included in WebsiteDefender WordPress Security:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Easy backup of WordPress database for disaster recovery</li>\n<li>Removal of error-information on login-page</li>\n<li>Addition of index.php to the wp-content, wp-content/plugins, wp-content/themes and wp-content/uploads directories to prevent directory listings</li>\n<li>Removal of wp-version, except in admin-area</li>\n<li>Removal of Really Simple Discovery meta tag</li>\n<li>Removal of Windows Live Writer meta tag</li>\n<li>Removal of core update information for non-admins</li>\n<li>Removal of plugin-update information for non-admins</li>\n<li>Removal of theme-update information for non-admins (only WP 2.8 and higher)</li>\n<li>Hiding of wp-version in backend-dashboard for non-admins</li>\n<li>Removal of version in URLs from scripts and stylesheets only on frontend</li>\n<li>Reporting of security overview after  Wordpress blog is scanned</li>\n<li>Reportig of file permissions following security checks</li>\n<li>Strong password generator tool to protect from brute force attacks</li>\n<li>Integrated tool to change the database prefix</li>\n<li>Disabling of database error reporting (if enabled)</li>\n<li>Disabling of PHP error reporting</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Apart from being extremely easy to use, the WebsiteDefender WordPress Security plugin runs in perfect harmony with WordPress and causes no impact on your site&#8217;s performance whatsoever. Accurate security checks and efficient reporting makes this plugin an absolute must-have if you take your site&#8217;s security as seriously as your online presence.</p>\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;\">Secure your site for free</span></p>\n<p>WebsiteDefender WordPress Security is available as a <a title=\"Download WebsiteDefender WordPress Security Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/websitedefender-wordpress-security\" target=\"_blank\">free download</a> and setting it up takes no longer than a few minutes. Remember, for a complete security audit and continuous monitoring of your site, you can sign up for the <a title=\"WebsiteDefender\" href=\"https://dashboard.websitedefender.com/register-for-free-website-scan.php\" target=\"_blank\">WebsiteDefender security service</a> for dynamic application scanning and vulnerability detection. WebsiteDefender is built on technology developed for <a title=\"Acunetix WVS\" href=\"http://www.acunetix.com\" target=\"_blank\">Acunetix WVS</a>, a pioneer in website security.</p>\n<p>To keep up to date with the latest security and technology news, join us on <a title=\"Follow WebsiteDefender on Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/WebsiteDefender\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> or <a title=\"Follow WebsiteDefender on Twitter\" href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/websitedefender\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>  and get in touch with us once in a while; we like to hear from you. If you have any questions about the new <a title=\"WP Security Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/websitedefender-wordpress-security\" target=\"_blank\">WebsiteDefender WordPress Security plugin</a> &#8211; or <a title=\"Wp Security Scan\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-security-scan/\" target=\"_blank\">WP Security Scan</a> and <a title=\"Secure WordPress\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/secure-wordpress\" target=\"_blank\">Secure WordPress</a> &#8211; feel free to comment below and we&#8217;ll get back to you as soon as we can.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/news/announcing-websitedefender-wordpress-security-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"Why does the automated agent copy fail, and how can I copy the agent manually?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/agent-installation-failure/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/agent-installation-failure/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 16 Aug 2011 15:31:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"FAQ\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/?p=1686\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:392:\"WebsiteDefender is also the owner of two popular WordPress plugins which provide active security monitoring of your WordPress blog or website: Secure WordPress WP Security Scan These plugins also provide the option to subscribe to the WebsiteDefender security service directly from your WordPress dashboard, with the additional functionality to download the Agent automatically and copy [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Jacques G\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3000:\"<p>WebsiteDefender is also the owner of two popular WordPress plugins which provide active security monitoring of your WordPress blog or website:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Secure WordPress\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/secure-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Secure WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WP-Security Scan\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-security-scan/\" target=\"_blank\">WP Security Scan</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>These plugins also provide the option to subscribe to the WebsiteDefender security service directly from your WordPress dashboard, with the additional functionality to download the Agent automatically and copy it in your site. This process has been known to fail as a result of specific WordPress site or user permissions which prevent background installs from running. Since it is impossible to cater for all types of site configurations, the WebsiteDefender Agent can also be downloaded and copied manually through the WebsiteDefender dashboard. Here&#8217;s how it&#8217;s done:</p>\n<ol>\n<ol>\n<li>Log in to your WebsiteDefender dashboard by navigating to <a title=\"WebsiteDefender Dashboard\" href=\"https://dashboard.websitedefender.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://dashboard.websitedefender.com/</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/01.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1688\" title=\"Access the WebsiteDefender dashboard\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/01-300x184.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /></a></p>\n<ol>\n<ol>\n<li>Click <strong>Go to website settings</strong> and then click the <strong>Scan Settings</strong> tab.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Download</strong> to obtain the Agent which you must upload to your site&#8217;s root directory. This can be done via FTP through your host&#8217;s admin console, or by using an <a title=\"Filezilla free FTP client\" href=\"http://filezilla-project.org/\" target=\"_blank\">FTP client</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/02.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1689\" title=\"Download the Agent\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/02-300x184.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /></a></p>\n<ol>\n<ol>\n<li>After you uploaded the Agent to your site, click <strong>Test</strong> to ensure that the Scanning Server can communicate with the agent.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/03.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1691\" title=\"Test the Agent installation\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/03-300x184.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/04.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1692\" title=\"Agent test result\" src=\"http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/04-300x184.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /> </a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"http://www.websitedefender.com/faq/agent-installation-failure/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s: