('302', '3', '2009-09-30 14:46:04', '2009-09-30 18:46:04', 'These sketches are a clear representation of my artist ability when I started my studies at <strong>McGill University</strong>. I had to take baby steps, and slowly find my own technique and style. I like these drawings because they are raw and true to myself, they haven\'t been worked and reworked, some of them were even completed in 30 seconds, all of them under 5 minutes. Not enough time to think, just to react. Using such a quick paced method really gets you in the mood to draw and I know that I wouldn\'t of had the confidence to draw full <strong>[intlink id=\"298\" type=\"post\"]portraits[/intlink]</strong> if I hadn\'t started small.\r\n\r\n[gallery=5]', 'Sketches from Freehand Drawing 1', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'sketches-freehand-drawing-1', '', '', '2011-07-15 15:42:25', '2011-07-15 19:42:25', '', '0', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/?p=302', '0', 'post', '', '0'),
