('308', '3', '2009-10-04 11:03:04', '2009-10-04 15:03:04', '<p>\r\nJust to state outright that I have never read \"Wind-up Bird Chronicle\" and all the following pieces of art were created on the impressions I received from a single passage extracted from this book. I just felt like a disclaimer was warranted, if it isn\'t it was still fun to write.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n Anyway, the below drawings are creations that spawned from reading a short exert of the Wind-up Bird Chronicle. They were all created in a different style, abstract, Escher inspired and clean perspective. Each was a different challenge and I am proud of how all three came out. Even though the perspective is out of place and removed from context (ie. it is a third person perspective derived from a first person narrative). \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWhat really came out from this project for me was a better understanding of space, and how it can be used in a two dimensional context, and that it can be even more interesting when these 2D images are transformed into a <strong>three dimensional creation</strong>.\r\n</p>\r\n[gallery=7]', 'Wind-up Bird Chronicle', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'windup-bird-chronicle', '', '', '2011-07-15 15:37:04', '2011-07-15 19:37:04', '', '0', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/?p=308', '0', 'post', '', '0'),
