('534', '3', '2011-08-23 15:50:54', '2011-08-23 19:50:54', '<p>\r\nThis portfolio was a personal project. I wanted to collected all my best work from 2009 and present it in a comprehensive format. Most of this work is from my <strong>Freehand Drawing</strong> class or my <strong>Architecture Studio</strong> class.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n[gview file=\"http://www.jacobhooey.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Personal-Portfolio.pdf\"]\r\n</p>', 'Personal Portfolio', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '510-revision-2', '', '', '2011-08-23 15:50:54', '2011-08-23 19:50:54', '', '510', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/510-revision-2.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('317', '3', '2011-07-15 14:55:22', '2011-07-15 18:55:22', '<p>\r\nThese sketches are a clear representation of my artist ability when I started my studies at <strong>McGill University</strong>. I had to take baby steps, and slowly find my own technique and style. I like these drawings because they are raw and true to myself, they haven\'t been worked and reworked, some of them were even completed in 30 seconds, all of them under 5 minutes. Not enough time to think, just to react. Using such a quick paced method really gets you in the mood to draw and I know that I wouldn\'t of had the confidence to draw full <strong>portraits</strong> if I hadn\'t started small.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n[gallery=5]', 'Sketches from Freehand Drawing 1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '302-revision-3', '', '', '2011-07-15 14:55:22', '2011-07-15 18:55:22', '', '302', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/302-revision-3.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('523', '3', '2011-08-23 16:08:15', '2011-08-23 20:08:15', '<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\r\nOn the Nature of Dynamical Instabilities in Interacting Binary Systems\r\nJacob Hooey\r\nJuly 28, 2009\r\nBishop\'s University\r\n&copy; 2009\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\r\nA thesis submitted in partial fulllment of the requirements for the degree\r\nof Bachelor of Science (Honours Physics)\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\r\nDepartment of Physics\r\nBishop\'s University\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center;\">Abstract</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin-left:35px; margin-right:35px;\">\r\nIn this thesis we will analyze the limits of stability in interacting binaries containing compact accretors. The specific case that will be used for this investigation is the case of <strong><a href=\"http://imagine.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/science/know_l2/cataclysmic_variables.html\">Cataclysmic Variables</a></strong> (CVs) in which the donor star is still on (or close to) the Zero Age Main Sequence (ZAMS) at the onset of mass transfer to the white dwarf. Roche lobe geometry and angular momentum dissipation play an integral part in affecting the stability of the CV\'s evolution. The CV is said to be dynamically unstable when the rate of mass transfer from the donor to the accretor increases precipitously until it exceeds the Eddington Limit. At this point, the accretion luminosity becomes greater than the Eddington luminosity and the accretor (white dwarf) cannot accrete further mass. At this point the two stars share a common envelope and most likely combine into one larger mass (this is known as a merger). We comprehensively delineate the initial conditions (mass of the donor and mass of the accretor) for which binaries are stable and unstable. We also find, for the first time, dynamical runaways which occur long after the initial phase of mass transfer $latex \\left(\\Delta m\\gtrsim0.1M_{\\odot}\\right)$. We label this behavior as a \"Latent Dynamical Instability\" (LDI). The conditions for which LDIs occur have also been mapped out and are shown to be strongly correlated with the internal structure of the donor star.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\r\nIf you want to read my full thesis you can download it <a href=\"/pdf/Honours_Thesis.pdf\">here</a>.\r\n</p>', 'Honours Thesis', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '71-revision', '', '', '2011-08-23 16:08:15', '2011-08-23 20:08:15', '', '71', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/71-revision.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('502', '3', '2011-08-23 14:56:09', '2011-08-23 18:56:09', '<p>\r\nThis portfolio was created from artwork that was completed while at Bishops University and a couple pieces of my earlier work. I used this collection of artwork to gain admittance in the McGill University Architecture program. The most difficult and interesting piece of art in this portfolio was the Hologram, which was developed in my Physics Lab class and took almost a semester to complete. This portfolio contains some of my best work and I plan on continuing to use it to showcase my artistic talent.\r\n</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<p>\r\ntest\r\n[gview file=\"http://www.jacobhooey.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio.pdf\"]\r\n</p>', 'McGill Entrance Portfolio', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '488-revision-2', '', '', '2011-08-23 14:56:09', '2011-08-23 18:56:09', '', '488', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/488-revision-2.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
