('603', '3', '2011-08-29 10:11:40', '2011-08-29 14:11:40', '<p>During my time at <a href=\"http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/index-eng.php\">Health Canada</a> I was added to the PeopleSoft Project. Our primary function was to oversea the migration from HR Advantage and the deployment of <a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/us/products/applications/peoplesoft-enterprise/index.html\">PeopleSoft</a>. Within this project my primary function was to create the organizational structure within PeopleSoft that would be the skeleton structure that would accept the migrated data. The two primary components that I worked with were the <a href=\"http://www.canada.gc.ca/depts/major/depind-eng.html\">Department Tree</a> structure as well as the <strong>Location Codes</strong> of the Health Canada and <a href=\"http://www.phac-aspc.gc.ca/index-eng.php\">Public Health Agency of Canada</a> facilities.</p>', 'PeopleSoft', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '109-revision', '', '', '2011-08-29 10:11:40', '2011-08-29 14:11:40', '', '109', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/109-revision.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('608', '3', '2011-08-29 10:50:37', '2011-08-29 14:50:37', '<p>Although my time at McGill University was brief, it was an amazing experience and helped me expand my creativity. I learned many things in such a short time it will be hard to describe them all. The main areas of study in the architecture program were Drawing, understanding space, a bit of history and structural engineering.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDrawing was a huge part of the program, every course I took had some drawing component to it. The two main courses that related primarily to the artistic side of architecture were Freehand Drawing and Architecture Studio. Freehand drawing was primarily focused on the artistic side of drawing while the Studio class focused more on drawing in relation to architecture. In both I developed a good knowledge of space and compositions as well as a better understanding of using an artistic medium to convey an idea. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When I said I learned a bit of history that was somewhat of an understatement. The History course offered at McGill was a dense analysis of the overall history of architecture, from the structures of ancient Egypt and Greece to the more modern <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:CLC_528_-_PARIS_-_Galerie_des_Machines.JPG\">La Galerie des Machines</a> in paris 1889. I also took a course on structures, which was essentially a history class but took the approach of analyzing the building methods and techniques used throughout history and how they relate to the buildings of today.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although I only spent a semester at McGill University I fell like I have received a rich education that will last for the rest of my life. </p>', 'McGill University', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '604-revision', '', '', '2011-08-29 10:50:37', '2011-08-29 14:50:37', '', '604', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/604-revision.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
