('632', '3', '2011-09-16 12:20:10', '2011-09-16 16:20:10', '<p>Recently, at work, I have been tasked to update our intranet telephone list from an SQL query to an LDAP query systems to reduce the amount of data entry needed when creating users. The challenge for me was more than a simple code and fix. The reason: I don\'t know ASP, LDAP Querying and VB and my SQL is very basic. Regardless I grab the bull by the horns and jumped in.</p>\n\n<p>During this project I learned ASP, how to query Active Directory using LDAP Queries, learned VB and integrating it into ASP documents and expanded my knowledge of both SQL and HTML.</p>\n\n<p>Another thing I learned, on a more personal level, is that I love to code. Taking on a challenge and writing a solution, running into problems and going line by line to find the problem. This type of work really gets my brain working and uses it solve any problem that gets in its way. Therefore I am going to make a greater effort from now on to expand my knowledge of languages, to start my own projects and to direct my career towards a programming position.</p>', 'ASP, LDAP and VB', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '629-autosave', '', '', '2011-09-16 12:20:10', '2011-09-16 16:20:10', '', '629', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/629-autosave.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('643', '3', '2011-09-16 15:05:22', '2011-09-16 19:05:22', '<a href=\"http://www.jacobhooey.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/BishopsUniversity.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.jacobhooey.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/BishopsUniversity-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"BishopsUniversity\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-640\" /></a><p><br>\r\nHaving been outside school and in the real world now for a couple I have had some time to reflect on my past experiences. Going to <a href=\'http://www.ubishops.ca/\'>Bishop\'s University</a> was one of those major life decisions that you either look back with fond memories or you might never want to look back at all. Luckily for me it was one of the best decisions I have ever made. Every single moment at Bishops was memorable and all those moments were enjoyable.</p><br>\r\n<p>What drew me to <a href=\'http://www.ubishops.ca/\'>Bishop\'s University</a> in the first place was its size. With an average student population of 2000 I felt it could be a great learning environment, this turned out to be truer than expected. The biggest class I ever attended contained 80 people, but even then by the end of the semester the teacher knew all our names. I found with such small classes (some with only 4 people) it was much easier to ask questions and approach the teacher for advice. Also Teachers were able to tailor their lesson plans to the needs of the students. All in all I found my education to be a great experience, one that I couldn\'t get in a class room of 1000</p><br>\r\n<p>\r\nAnother thing about unique to <a href=\'http://www.ubishops.ca/\'>Bishop\'s University</a> where the unique opportunities to join the world of academia professionally. The first of these opportunities was a position as Teacher\'s Assistant for two of my professors. I would correct assignments and would assist in managing the students assignments as a whole. The second, and even greater opportunity, was an <a href=\'http://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/Students-Etudiants/UG-PC/USRA-BRPC_eng.asp\'>USRA scholarship</a> that allowed me to work during the summer as a Research Assistant for Dr. Lorne Nelson. I did work helping a masters student write his thesis, helped build a website for a division of CHEAR (Canadian High-Energy Astrophysics Research). This was an invaluable experience that provided me great insight into the world of academia.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOverall Bishop\'s University was an experience that was critical in creating the man I am today. For anyone looking at different universities I give Bishop\'s University a very strong recommendation.\r\n</p>', 'Bishop\'s University', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '617-revision', '', '', '2011-09-16 15:05:22', '2011-09-16 19:05:22', '', '617', 'http://www.jacobhooey.com/617-revision.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
